Stats API is all about.

00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:16.430
Because the Player Stats
API will automatically

00:01:16.430 --> 00:01:19.720
categorize your players
according to three segments--

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:22.700
how much they spend in your
game, their engagement,

00:01:22.700 --> 00:01:24.810
and their progression
in their game.

00:01:24.810 --> 00:01:27.630
This allows you to
take real time action

00:01:27.630 --> 00:01:29.080
when it matters the most.

00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:32.410
For example, you can give
gifts and free upgrades

00:01:32.410 --> 00:01:35.430
to the players that spend
the most money in your game.

00:01:35.430 --> 00:01:37.530
And for highly
engaged players, you

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:39.410
could give them
stuff as a reward

00:01:39.410 --> 00:01:41.420
for recruiting new players.

00:01:41.420 --> 00:01:45.920
And for players that get stuck
and can't make any progress,

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:49.880
you should really give them
a hand and provide a hint.

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:52.220
So start turning all
of this information

00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:54.350
that it gives you to actions.

00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:56.820
Because this is not
only valuable to you

00:01:56.820 --> 00:02:00.700
as the developers, it's also a
great thing for your players.

